# Add any other libraries here
# load your data 
AVONET3_BirdTree <- read_excel("data/AVONET3_BirdTree.xlsx", 
    sheet = "AVONET3_BirdTree")
Bird_data <- AVONET3_BirdTree %>%
  select(Species3, Total.individuals, Beak.Length_Culmen, Habitat, Trophic.Level, Trophic.Niche, Mass) %>%
  filter(Total.individuals >= 5)
 

Total_Habitat <- Bird_data %>%
  group_by(Habitat) %>%
  summarise(total.birds = sum(Total.individuals)) %>%
  filter(Habitat != "NA")



ggplot(data  = Total_Habitat, 
       aes(x = Habitat,
           y = total.birds,
           fill = Habitat)) +
         geom_col() +
  theme_minimal() +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, size = 10)) +
      scale_fill_brewer(type = "div",
                        palette = 9,
                        direction = 1,
                        aesthetics = "fill") +
  labs(title = "Total bird count within each habitat",
       x = "Habitat",
       y = "Total Birds")

expl.stats_birds <- Bird_data %>%
  group_by(Trophic.Level) %>%
  summarise(avg_culmen.length = mean(Beak.Length_Culmen,),
         avg_mass = mean(Mass)) %>%
  select(Trophic.Level, avg_culmen.length, avg_mass)
total_trophic <- AVONET3_BirdTree %>%
  group_by(Trophic.Level) %>%
  summarise(total.birds = n()) %>%
  filter(Trophic.Level != "NA")

pink <- c("#FFC4D6", "#FFA6C1", "#FF87AB", "#FF5D8F")

ggplot(data = total_trophic,
       aes(x = Trophic.Level,
           y = total.birds,
           fill = Trophic.Level)) +
  geom_col() +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = pink) +
  labs(title = "Total bird count within each Trophic Level",
       x = "Trophic Level",
       y = "Total Birds")

#forest birds data plot

forest_data <- AVONET3_BirdTree %>%
  select(Species3, Total.individuals, Beak.Length_Culmen, Habitat, Trophic.Level, Trophic.Niche) %>%
  filter(Habitat == "Forest")

total_trophic <- AVONET3_BirdTree %>%
  group_by(Trophic.Level) %>%
  summarise(total.birds = sum(Total.individuals)) %>%
  slice(c(-3))

forest_data <- left_join(total_trophic, Bird_data) %>%
  select(-Total.individuals)
## Joining with `by = join_by(Trophic.Level)`
green_shades <- c("#75975E", "#95BB72", "#B3CF99", "#DDEAD1")
green_shades <- green_shades[1:length(unique(Bird_data$Trophic.Niche))]


ggplot(data = total_trophic,
       mapping = aes(x = Trophic.Level,
                     y = total.birds,
                     fill = Trophic.Level)) +
  geom_col() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = green_shades) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10, angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  labs(title = "Number of Birds in each Trophic Level",
       subtitle = "Forest Habitat",
       x = "Trophic Level",
       y = "Number of Birds")

ggplot(data = forest_data,
       mapping = aes( x = Trophic.Level,
                      y = Beak.Length_Culmen,
                      fill = Trophic.Level)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = green_shades) +
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10, angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  labs(title = "Culmen length of each trophic level",
       subtitle = "Forest Habitat",
       x = "Trophic Level",
       y= "Beak Length Culmen")

#box plots of all the habitats' beak culmen length against trophic levels

mean_culmen <- Bird_data %>%
  group_by(Habitat, Trophic.Level) %>%
  summarise(mean_culmen = mean(Beak.Length_Culmen, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  ungroup()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Habitat'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
clean_data <- Bird_data %>%
  filter(
    !is.na(Habitat),
    !is.na(Trophic.Level),
    Trophic.Level != "NA",
    Habitat != "NA"
  )

ggplot(
  data= clean_data %>%
    filter(!is.na(Habitat), !is.na(Trophic.Level)),
  aes(x = Trophic.Level,
      y = Beak.Length_Culmen,
      fill = Trophic.Level)
  ) +
  
  geom_boxplot(outlier.size = 0.8) +
  facet_wrap(~ Habitat, ncol = 3, scales = "free_y") +
  scale_y_log10() +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 10) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 7, angle = 20),
        strip.text = element_text(size = 10, face = "bold"),
        legend.position = "bottom") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = blue) +
  labs(
    title = "Culmen Beak Length across different Trophic Levels",
    subtitle = "Seperated by Habitat",
    x = "Trophic Level",
    y = "Log of the Culmen Beak Length"
  )

birds.data_mass <- Bird_data %>%
  select(Species3, Total.individuals, Beak.Length_Culmen, Habitat, Mass, Trophic.Level)%>%
  mutate(Mass_kg = Mass/1000,
         log_mass_kg = log(Mass_kg), log_culmen = log(Beak.Length_Culmen)) %>%
   filter(Trophic.Level != "NA")

size_data <- mutate(Bird_data,
                    size =
                    factor(case_when(
                      Beak.Length_Culmen < 20.0 ~ "small",
                      Beak.Length_Culmen >= 20.0 ~ "big"
                      )))

set.seed(123)

bird_split <- initial_split(size_data, prop = 0.80)

train_data <- training(bird_split)
test_data  <- testing(bird_split)

bird_rec <- recipe(
  size ~ Habitat + Trophic.Level + Mass,       
  data = train_data 
  ) %>%
  step_dummy(all_nominal(), -all_outcomes())

summary(bird_rec)
## # A tibble: 4  4
##   variable      type      role      source  
##   <chr>         <list>    <chr>     <chr>   
## 1 Habitat       <chr [3]> predictor original
## 2 Trophic.Level <chr [3]> predictor original
## 3 Mass          <chr [2]> predictor original
## 4 size          <chr [3]> outcome   original
bird_mod <- logistic_reg() %>%
  set_engine("glm")


bird_wkflow <- workflow() %>% 
  add_model(bird_mod) %>% 
  add_recipe(bird_rec)

bird_fit <- bird_wkflow %>%
  fit(data = train_data)
## Warning: glm.fit: fitted probabilities numerically 0 or 1 occurred
bird_pred <- predict(bird_fit, test_data, type = "prob") %>% 
  bind_cols(test_data)

cutoff_prob <- 0.5

  mutate(
    size      = if_else(size == "small", "Bird beak is small", "Bird beak is big"),
    size_pred = if_else(.pred_small > cutoff_prob, "Bird beak labelled as small", "Bird beak labelled as big")
    ) %>%
  count(size_pred, size) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = size, values_from = n)
